Messages.Text: heart

Heart health tests include procedures to assess the functioning of the heart and identify potential issues. These tests may include cholesterol checks, blood pressure monitoring, and advanced imaging techniques.
lung

Lung diseases affect the ability of the lungs to function properly. These diseases include asthma, COPD, infections like pneumonia, and lung cancer. Symptoms often include shortness of breath, chronic cough, and difficulty breathing.

brain

Neurology is the branch of medicine that deals with the diagnosis and treatment of disorders of the nervous system. This includes diseases affecting the brain, spinal cord, nerves, and muscles. Neurological conditions can range from common ailments like headaches and migraines to more severe disorders such as epilepsy, stroke, and neurodegenerative diseases.
eye

The practice of ophthalmology provides patients with total eye care. This includes disease prevention; refractive and optical services; diagnosis and management of eye disease; plus medical, surgical, and rehabilitative services.
asthma

Asthma is a chronic lung disease that inflames and narrows the airways. It causes recurring periods of wheezing, chest tightness, shortness of breath, and coughing. Triggers include allergens, exercise, or irritants like smoke.
